lenders.name: Valori Lyles
lenders.occupational_info:
Valori Lyles left her career as a language arts teacher- which she very much loved and enjoyed- in order to travel for a great deal of time within Central America.  During these travels, Valori Lyles called San Jose, Costa Rica her home, but she went to a great deal of other nations, such as Cuba, Panama and Nicaragua.  Valori Lyles has recently returned from her travels and is back living in the United States, getting re-acclimated to life in the states and visiting family she has not seen.  

Valori Lyles decided to travel to Central America in order to learn about the local culture, improve upon her Spanish and have some incredible life experiences.  Valori Lyles greatly enjoyed her time abroad and feels very fortunate to have had the opportunity to see such beautiful, incredible places.
